    <!-- Help/APP -->
    <string name="help_app_intro">Using the map</string>
    <string name="help_app_1">The interactive map and the search engine allow you to find spots where parking is allowed for the time period you need.</string>
    <string name="help_app_2">Tap on a parking post, displayed in green, to display the next no-parking period in that area.</string>
    <string name="help_app_3">Zones where parking is forbidden are hidden from the map.</string>
    <string name="help_app_4">Tap the date at the screen bottom to select the time period for which you need a parking spot.</string>
    <string name="help_app_5">Hint: Long press on the map to change your geographic location.</string>

    <!-- Help/Rules -->
    <string name="help_rules">It is prohibited to park:\r\n&#8226; in front of a private driveway\r\n&#8226; in a back lane\r\n&#8226; on a cycle path\r\n&#8226; next to a parked vehicle (double parking)\r\n&#8226; facing oncoming traffic\r\n&#8226; in front of a fire hydrant\r\n&#8226; near an intersection\r\n&#8226; on the sidewalk\r\n&#8226; in a pedestrian walkway\r\n&#8226; in front of a disability access ramp\r\n&#8226; on an angle, unless signage, even owing to snowfall</string>

    <!-- Help/NoStopping -->
    <string name="help_stopping_1">No stopping any time.</string>
    <string name="help_stopping_2">No stopping during the period specified.</string>
    <string name="help_stopping_3">No stopping any time: Reserved for emergency vehicles.</string>
    <string name="help_stopping_4">No stopping any time: Reserved for buses.</string>

    <!-- Help/NoParking -->
    <string name="help_parking_1">No parking any time.</string>
    <string name="help_parking_2">No parking during the period and season specified.</string>
    <string name="help_parking_3">No parking during the period specified: Reserved for taxis.</string>
    <string name="help_parking_6">No parking during the period specified: This temporary sign takes priority over the existing signage.</string>

    <!-- Help/Restricted -->
    <string name="help_restricted_1">Maximum 15 minute parking: Load/Unload area.</string>
    <string name="help_restricted_2">Maximum 60 minute parking, during the period specified.</string>

    <!-- Help/SRRR -->
    <string name="help_srrr_1">No parking during the period specified: Reserved for S3R permit holders (resident parking only).</string>
    <string name="help_srrr_2">The number of parking spaces reserved for residents in a given sector is no more than 50% of the available spaces.</string>

    <!-- Help/Cell phone -->
    <string name="help_cell_1">As of April 1, 2008, use of a hand-held cell phone that does not have a “hands-free” function is prohibited while driving. Committing this type of offence will result in:\r\n&#8226; 3 demerit points\r\n&#8226; $80 to $100 fine</string>

    <!-- Help/Arrow -->
    <string name="help_arrow_1">If the sign carries an arrow, the regulation applies in the zone pointed by the arrow.\r\n\r\nThe zone ends at the next intersection or at a sign that carries an arrow.</string>
    <string name="help_arrow_2">An arrow pointing <b>towards the road</b> indicates the beginning of the sign’s zone:</string>
    <string name="help_arrow_3">An arrow pointing <b>towards the sidewalk</b> indicates the end of the sign’s zone:</string>
    <string name="help_arrow_4">A sign without an arrow is an intermediate sign that indicates the middle of the regulation zone.\r\n\r\nA regulation zone can begin after an intersection, in which case the sign doesn’t carry an arrow.</string>
    <string name="help_arrow_7">A back lane does not interrupt the signage: if there are no other signs, the signage still applies on the other side of the lane.</string>

    <!-- Help/Priority -->
    <string name="help_priority_1">When a pole carries multiple signs, regulations are applied from top to bottom signs.</string>
    <string name="help_priority_2">Two examples, applying different priorities to the same signs:</string>
    <string name="help_priority_3">Case #1: it’s 8:00 Monday morning, you want to park for 30&#160;minutes.\r\n\r\nThe sign on top rules, so parking is strictly forbidden between 7:00 and 9:00, regardless of duration.\r\n\r\n= Parking forbidden</string>
    <string name="help_priority_4">Case #2: signs are in reverse order. It’s still 8:00 Monday morning, you want to park for 30&#160;minutes.\r\n\r\nHere, maximum 60 minute parking is allowed on weekdays.\r\n\r\n= Parking allowed</string>

